Package alex.mojaki.boxes.observers.change

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ChangeObserver<T>
    A PowerBox can apply a list of these objects after the value of a box changes, typically to incur some side effect such as logging or to throw an exception if the value is invalid.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ChangePrinter
    Print to standard out changes made to the box this is added to.
    RequireBounds<T>
    If the value is beyond the given bounds, or if it is equal to a bound that is not inclusive throw an IllegalArgumentException.
    TargetedChangeObserver<T,V>
    A ChangeObserver which can associate specific objects with boxes, to overcome the fact that boxes share observers in a family rather than each storing their own.
    ThrowOnNull
    Throws an IllegalArgumentException when the value changes to null.
